查理·考夫曼批评工作室老板“恶心”的薪酬方案https://www.nme.com/news/film/charlie-kaufman-criticises-studio-bosses-over-disgusting-pay-packages-3485337?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=charlie-kaufman-criticises-studio-bosses-令人厌恶的薪酬方案Hollie GeraghtySat, 19 Aug 2023 12:37:15 +0000 Film NewsNews https://www.nme.com/?p=3485337 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/charlie-kaufman-criticises-studio-bosses.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="查理·考夫曼" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/charlie-kaufman-criticises-studio-bosses.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/charlie-kaufman-criticises-studio-bosses-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/charlie-kaufman-criticises-studio-bosses-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/charlie-kaufman-criticises-studio-bosses-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/charlie-kaufman-criticises-studio-bosses-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/charlie-kaufman-criticises-studio-bosses-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> “他们对艺术形式造成了损害”</p><p>查理<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/charlie-kaufman-criticises-studio-bosses-over-disgusting-pay-packages-3485337">·考夫曼 (Charlie Kaufman) 批评工作室老板“恶心”的薪酬方案</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">《NME》</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/charlie-kaufman-criticises-studio-bosses.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="查理·考夫曼" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/charlie-kaufman-criticises-studio-bosses.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/charlie-kaufman-criticises-studio-bosses-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/charlie-kaufman-criticises-studio-bosses-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/charlie-kaufman-criticises-studio-bosses-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/charlie-kaufman-criticises-studio-bosses-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/charlie-kaufman-criticises-studio-bosses-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>查理·考夫曼（Charlie Kaufman）抨击好莱坞制片厂老板的利润和薪酬“令人作呕”，而他们却“什么也不做”。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/film-features/strike-actors-writers-hollywood-when-will-it-end-3477098">好莱坞罢工！关于演员和作家抗议的每个问题都得到了解答</a></strong></li></ul><p>这位奥斯卡获奖编剧本周在萨拉热窝电影节上发表讲话，他指出高管们的薪酬将利润置于艺术之上。</p><p> “这很恶心，因为他们什么也没做，”考夫曼告诉<em><a href="https://variety.com/2023/film/global/charlie-kaufman-strikes-studio-ceo-salary-1235699455/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">《综艺》杂志</a></em>。 “不，他们所做的就是造成伤害。它们对艺术形式造成了损害。通过这样做，他们对人类造成了损害。如果一切都是为了他们的底线和省钱，那么艺术形式就没有什么了。”</p><p>这位编剧在萨拉热窝领取终身成就奖时，被发现穿着一件写着“作家协会罢工”的 T 恤。 <em>Variety</em>报道称，在接受采访时，他露出了第二层，里面是一件 WGA 品牌的 T 恤。 </p><figure id="attachment_3477201" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3477201" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3477201" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Hollywood_Strikes_Los_Angeles.jpg" alt="罢工" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Hollywood_Strikes_Los_Angeles.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Hollywood_Strikes_Los_Angeles-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Hollywood_Strikes_Los_Angeles-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Hollywood_Strikes_Los_Angeles-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Hollywood_Strikes_Los_Angeles-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Hollywood_Strikes_Los_Angeles-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3477201" class="wp-caption-text">图片来源：盖蒂</figcaption></figure><p>考夫曼在周一（8 月 14 日）的大师班上发表讲话时还表示，艺术与“传统好莱坞美食”之间的区别是“真理与废话之间的区别”。</p><p> “工作室将继续存在，人们将继续制造垃圾，因为垃圾在这一点上......可以发财，”他说。</p><p>考夫曼在接受<em>Variety</em>采访时详细阐述道：“[工作室负责人]的存在并不会带来任何美丽的作品。他们的做法与此相反。我认为好莱坞制作的影片就证明了这一点，一部电影越贵，它对文化的价值就越小，”他说。</p><p>当被问及他是否认为制片厂老板太脱节而无法完全理解劳资谈判时，他说：“我认为他们掌握了这一点。我认为他们知道他们的钱来自于其他人没有得到钱。” </p><figure id="attachment_3473294" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3473294" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3473294" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Hollywood-actors-strike-2.jpg" alt="好莱坞罢工" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Hollywood-actors-strike-2.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Hollywood-actors-strike-2-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Hollywood-actors-strike-2-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Hollywood-actors-strike-2-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Hollywood-actors-strike-2-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Hollywood-actors-strike-2-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3473294" class="wp-caption-text">库梅尔·南贾尼 (Kumail Nanjiani) 和他的妻子艾米丽·V·戈登 (Emily V. Gordon) 罢工 图片来源：CHRIS DELMAS/AFP via Getty Images</figcaption></figure><p>好莱坞作家和演员<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/why-are-actors-striking-in-hollywood-3468340">目前同时就流媒体时代的基本工资和剩余费用以及针对该行业使用人工智能的保障措施等问题进行了罢工</a>。</p><p>这是60多年来首次演员和作家同时罢工。</p><p> 《<em>一尘不染的心灵的永恒阳光》</em>编剧的评论是在<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/mark-ruffalo-criticises-hollywood-fat-cats-amid-actors-strike-3469562">马克·鲁法洛批评好莱坞“肥猫”</a> “创造了亿万富翁帝国并认为我们不再有价值”之后发表的。</p><p>查理<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/charlie-kaufman-criticises-studio-bosses-over-disgusting-pay-packages-3485337">·考夫曼 (Charlie Kaufman) 批评工作室老板“恶心”的薪酬方案</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">《NME》</a>上。</p> ;
